name: Get Virtual Apps Session Response Time
description: Retrieves user experience statistics from the current Citrix Virtual Applications sessions and categorize them as good, acceptable or degraded according to their response time.

inputs.description: Maximum random delay set to avoid network overload. Provide number of seconds lower than 600
inputs.name: MaximumDelayInSeconds

inputs.description: Maximum value in milliseconds below which round-trip time user experience is considered as good. Provide number of milliseconds lower than 10000
inputs.name: GoodThreshold

inputs.description: Maximum value in milliseconds below which round-trip time user experience is considered as acceptable. Provide number of milliseconds lower than 10000 and greater than GoodThreshold
inputs.name: AcceptableThreshold

inputs.description: Comma-separated list of IPv4 subnets to define a connection like internal. They must be listed in [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classless_Inter-Domain_Routing CIDR notation]
inputs.name: InternalSubnetsList

inputs.description: Comma-separated list of IPv4 subnets to define a connection like VPN. They must be listed in [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classless_Inter-Domain_Routing CIDR notation]
inputs.name: VPNSubnetsList

outputs.description: Total count of user sessions with round-trip time below the GoodThreshold value
outputs.name: GoodUserExperienceSessions

outputs.description: Total count of user sessions with round-trip time between GoodThreshold and AcceptableThreshold values
outputs.name: AcceptableUserExperienceSessions

outputs.description: Total count of user sessions with round-trip time exceeding the AcceptableThreshold value
outputs.name: DegradedUserExperienceSessions

outputs.description: Ratio of degraded user sessions vs all user sessions
outputs.name: DegradedUserExperienceSessionsRatio

outputs.description: List of properties of degraded user experience sessions, separated by colon. Each list item will describe separate user session. The expected output format is CSV
outputs.name: DegradedSessionsDetails

outputs.description: Ratio of degraded user sessions when the connection type is External (not internal nor VPN)
outputs.name: DegradedUserExperienceExternalSessionsRatio

outputs.description: Ratio of degraded user sessions when the connection type is VPN
outputs.name: DegradedUserExperienceVPNSessionsRatio
